reviewList.text: Richard Acosta is as professional as they come and a man of his word. We had serious front end damage to our 1999 Land Cruiser and parts were hard to come by. Richard and his crew made it look like new. The color matched perfectly and he made sure we were satisfied and happy. His first priority is the customer. If you need any paint work or body work don't take my word for it. Meet Richard at Spraymasters and you'll know.

ATTENTION: UNETHICAL BUSINESS. THIS PLACE PRACTICES PRICE GOUGING. Seems like they will do anything for an extra dollar. Very unhelpful on the phone, and also very curt, to the point of being rude. I have patronized this restaurant multiple times but will probably not return after my experience on Super Bowl Sunday.

Olive Garden used to be good but the quality has really taken a turn for the worse over the last few years. The breadsticks taste like they were previously frozen and are unnaturally chewy. Spaghetti with meat sauce was fair. The salad was decent, even though it's just ice berg lettuce with a high fructose corn syrup dressing. I got the gnocchi chicken soup, which is probably the most awful soup I've ever tasted. It was like seawater with cream in it. The gnocchi were flavorless. The chicken was gristly. Overall, this was a very disappointing meal and it's overpriced as well. I will never be visiting another Olive Garden again.

Atmosphere overall was good. Music wasn't too loud. However, extremely slow service. I think our waiter was basically retarded. Wings were cooked well, but there was VERY little sauce on them and you could barely taste the favors. The fries were finally brought out 15 minutes after we got the wings. Took literally 30 minutes to bring the check afterwe asked them. Very disappointing. This chain has gone down hill.

Atmosphere, food and service is good but not cheap. $$ not.Also watching multiple games on their big screen is terrible. They do not use the whole screen surface. They configure the screen to where there is one main screen with 3 small ones. Bad if you if your NFL TIX game is not the main one showing. However, it works with no complains if the 'Cats are playing.

I've been here before several times and enjoyed the atmosphere, food and service. However, the last time we were there we were cut-off and shown to the door. Been there for couple of hours, our shift-changing waitress Lindsy was friendly at first introducing herself. Later we innocently got her name wrong signaling for her and she overreacted. She was quick at the trigger and should have used more discretion.

BOYCOTT THIS LOCATION. IT'S owed by bigot racist owners. I find it ironic that the "Christian" owners of this store are hateful against Hispanics when their store is IN THE HEART of the Hispanic community lol. Seriously boycott these guys.Los dueños son unos pinches racistas, no compren aqui.

Today's special is Monte Carlo sandwich w/ German potato salad and watermelon. Super delicious. This being my first visit, my experience was excellent. I'll definitely come back here to try more. Very friendly and helpful staff. I was greeted immediately after I walked in. I didn't get the look-up-and-then-ill-go-back-to-what-i'm-doing thing that restaurants dish out all too frequently nowadays. Food came out quickly and well presented. This is a small restaurant with limited self-seating inside and out. I had my hands full, so when I was about to take outside seating, the girl carried my lunch outside for me. Wonderful! This spot is a must try.
